1784410282484061	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErfw		item.comment	bn-2sv	{"body":"Implemented the disposable topology and capability planner. Added a stdlib-only sippycup_chaos package and sippycup-chaos CLI with read-only rootless/rootful, effective NET_ADMIN, Podman/iproute2/tc, netem, IFB, classifier, and MTU detection; tri-state unknowns fail closed. The versioned no-change plan defines test0, imp-test0, imp-uplink0, and uplink0 across test/impairment/uplink namespaces; maps egress to imp-uplink0 and ingress to imp-test0; supports independent asymmetric attachment without IFB; freezes canonical literal CIDRs with dst matching outbound and src matching inbound; hashes scope and pre-mutation route/qdisc snapshots; refuses existing namespaces; and emits no mutation commands. Added separately named dangerous-host-network mode requiring rootful NET_ADMIN, dedicated-test-vm:NAME confirmation, a concrete existing host interface, and IFB for ingress. Added JSON schema, architecture/privilege/packet-path docs, README/Makefile integration, and container/smoke packaging. Verification: 10 focused topology tests pass; 70 topology+campaign+runtime+integration/exit-gate tests pass; Python compileall, schema JSON parsing, CLI help/capability JSON, and shell checks pass. The real read-only host probe reports rootless mode and correctly sees NET_ADMIN unavailable. A broad 83-test run had 82 passes plus one unrelated concurrent media-canary license-text assertion failure; no topology failure. No network mutation or external traffic was performed."}	blake3:9V3NEmp6b4QwHAUBx_2FplmYRCokM9QlZBBndFgUnpA
