1784410493478884	campaign_runtime	itc:v3:AWKfOZmeTnzMQAAAAAAAQb7tt677YAAAAAEsFQ		item.comment	bn-3h6	{"body":"Implemented deterministic constrained coverage in lib/sippycup/covering.py. Covering arrays classify every requested global t-way and risk-specific higher-strength tuple by constraint extendability, retain required/excluded ledgers with reasons, emit mandatory rows first, deterministically greedily cover all permitted tuples, accept stable non-negative seeds, and bound the ledger at 250,000 tuples. Matrix strength now defaults to pairwise; risk annotations can select coveringFactors plus a strictly higher interactionStrength. Ordered action generation covers permitted ordered subsequences for DTMF/hold/resume/re-INVITE/failure/recovery/hangup, enforces resume-after-hold, recover-after-failure, terminal hangup, and deterministic seeds. Docs/schema/Ferivox sample updated. Evidence: 5 generator property tests plus 8 matrix tests PASS; brute-force small-model oracle exactly matches required tuples; forbidden tuples appear in no row; same seed is identical and different seeds preserve coverage; focused campaign/matrix/covering/runtime suite 53 PASS; complete non-oracle regression 91 PASS; oracle suite 79 PASS plus 20k benchmark 1.461826s/3,942,782-byte peak PASS; compileall PASS. Ferivox: 590,490 Cartesian rows reduced to 30 rows covering 636 required tuples with 16 excluded; sequence suite 10 traces covers 42 ordered pairs with 7 excluded. Runnable-case materialization and budget-truncation reporting remain intentionally assigned to dependent bn-1z5."}	blake3:sgy8hrwPGtz4w8ALvTapZMSDuhjSLyXO1jSf4Hv4S30
